        <section id="hardware">
            <title>Supported Hardware</title>
            <p>The following servers are supported for the lifecycle manager host, and for the
                controllers and compute servers.</p>
            <p><b id="hlm">Lifecycle Manager Host</b> The lifecycle manager host is a single server
                with at least a 2TB Disk, 128GB RAM and 2 physical CPUs. The CPUs must meet the
                specifications in <xref href="#topic1773cgsmd/specs" format="dita">the Required
                    Specifications table below</xref>.</p>
            <p id="controllers"><b>Controllers and compute servers</b> The following servers are
                supported for the controllers and compute servers in the <xref
                    href="../../Overview/carrier-grade-overview-kvm.dita#topic1743cgok">KVM
                    region</xref>. The servers must meet the specifications in <xref
                    href="#topic1773cgsmd/specs" format="dita">the Required Specifications table
                    below</xref>.</p>
            <p><b>Controller:</b></p>
            <ul id="ul_qf5_vbp_y5">
                <li>DL360 (Gen 9 or Gen 8)</li>
                <li>DL380 (Gen 9 or Gen 8)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><b>Compute:</b></p>
            <ul id="ul_rf5_vbp_y5">
                <li>DL360 (Gen 9 or Gen 8)</li>
                <li>DL380 (Gen 9 or Gen 8)</li>
                <li>BL460 (Gen 9 or Gen 8)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><b>Notes:</b>
                <ul id="ul_mxb_gzd_ss">
                    <li>You must update the firmware to HPE Service Pack for ProLiant (SPP) Version
                        2015.10.0.</li>
                    <li>If you are using Gen8 systems, you will experience reduced performance.</li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
