        <section id="hardware-config">
            <title>Required Hardware Configurations </title>
            <p>The servers, selected from the <xref href="#topic1773cgsmd/hardware" format="dita"
                    >Supported Hardware</xref> lists, must be configured as follows for HPE Helion
                OpenStack Carrier Grade.</p>
            <p>One (1) <b>Lifecycle Manager Host</b>. You must have a server with a 2TB Disk and 128
                GB RAM, and 2 physical CPUs for the lifecycle manager host. This server will also
                host three (3) virtual machines that serve as controllers for HPE Helion OpenStack
                Carrier Grade. Each of the controller nodes requires at least 200GB of virtual disk,
                32GB of virtual memory, and 4 virtual CPUs. The amount of memory required depends
                upon the types of applications being run on the cloud.. You can add additional
                memory for each controller, as needed, during the installation.</p>
            <p id="kvm-config">Two (2) <b>KVM Region controllers</b>. You must have two (2)
                baremetal systems to install the KVM Region controllers. For systems with multiple
                NICs, only one NIC may be active or connected. </p>
            <p>Two (2) or more <b>KVM Region compute servers</b>. You must have at least two (2)
                baremetal system to install the KVM Region compute servers.</p>
            <ul id="ul_lwc_ltz_jt">
